                },
                {
                    "type": "note",
                    "content": "<b>Pro Tip:</b> Preposition के बाद हमेशा <b>Noun</b> या <b>Pronoun (Object Form: me, him, her, us, them)</b> आता है!"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "7️⃣ Conjunction (समुच्चयबोधक)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "दो <b>शब्दों, वाक्यांशों या वाक्यों</b> को जोड़ने वाले शब्द को <b>Conjunction</b> कहते हैं।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "📋 Types of Conjunction",
                        "headers": ["Type", "Examples", "Usage"],
                        "rows": [
                            ["<b>Coordinating</b>", "and, but, or, nor, for, yet, so", "Equal importance के 2 भाग जोड़ता है (FANBOYS)"],
                            ["<b>Subordinating</b>", "because, if, when, while, although, unless", "Main + Dependent clause जोड़ता है"],
                            ["<b>Correlative</b>", "either...or, neither...nor, both...and, not only...but also", "Pairs में इस्तेमाल होता है"]
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "🔑 FANBOYS - Coordinating Conjunctions",
                        "headers": ["Letter", "Conjunction", "Example"],
                        "rows": [
                            ["<b>F</b>", "For", "I was tired, <b>for</b> I had worked all day."],
                            ["<b>A</b>", "And", "She is smart <b>and</b> beautiful."],
                            ["<b>N</b>", "Nor", "He neither drinks <b>nor</b> smokes."],
                            ["<b>B</b>", "But", "I tried <b>but</b> failed."],
                            ["<b>O</b>", "Or", "Tea <b>or</b> coffee?"],
                            ["<b>Y</b>", "Yet", "He is poor <b>yet</b> honest."],
                            ["<b>S</b>", "So", "It was late, <b>so</b> I went home."]
