                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "🔴 Common Confusions",
                        "headers": ["Confusion", "Clarification", "Examples"],
                        "rows": [
                            ["<b>Adjective vs Adverb</b>", "Adjective → Noun का वर्णन<br>Adverb → Verb/Adj/Adv का वर्णन", "<b>beautiful</b> girl (Adj)<br>She sings <b>beautifully</b> (Adv)"],
                            ["<b>Noun vs Verb</b>", "Same शब्द दोनों बन सकता है!", "I <b>play</b> cricket. (Verb)<br>The <b>play</b> was amazing. (Noun)"],
                            ["<b>Preposition vs Conjunction</b>", "Prep = Noun से पहले<br>Conj = Clauses/Words जोड़ता है", "<b>Before</b> lunch (Prep)<br><b>Before</b> I came, he left. (Conj)"],
                            ["<b>This/That - Pronoun vs Adjective</b>", "Alone = Pronoun<br>Before Noun = Adjective", "<b>This</b> is my book. (Pronoun)<br><b>This</b> book is mine. (Adjective)"],
                            ["<b>Possessive Pronoun vs Possessive Adjective</b>", "Adj + Noun = Possessive Adj<br>Alone = Possessive Pronoun", "<b>My</b> book (Adj)<br>It is <b>mine</b>. (Pronoun)"],
                            ["<b>good vs well</b>", "good = Adjective<br>well = Adverb", "He is a <b>good</b> singer.<br>He sings <b>well</b>."]
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "🔍 Word Identification Trick",
            "content": [
